title: Treasury Bill Yields Jump to Highest Level Since 2013 on Debt Ceiling Worries
text:
A selloff in U.S. short-term government debt deepened on Monday, sending some yields to a two-year high, amid growing concerns about a renewed stalemate among lawmakers over raising the nationâ€™s debt ceiling.
Investors had lightened up on holdings of a couple of bills maturing in November Friday. The selling pressure on Monday spread to all the bills maturing during the course of next month.
